# Tool State Persistence

Every tool component must persist user-editable content (text inputs, editor contents, selected options) to localStorage so state survives page reloads.

## How

Use the shared `usePersistedState` hook instead of `useState` for any value the user can edit:

```jsx
import { usePersistedState } from "../../hooks/use-persisted-state";

const [code, setCode] = usePersistedState("my-tool-code", DEFAULT_CODE);
const [mode, setMode] = usePersistedState("my-tool-mode", "default");
```

## Key naming

- Keys are automatically prefixed with `rha-tools-` by the hook.
- Use the pattern `<tool-slug>-<field>`, e.g. `"diff-textA"`, `"js-sandbox-code"`, `"openapi-spec"`.

## What to persist

- Editor / textarea contents
- Dropdown or toggle selections that affect behaviour (diff mode, selected schema, etc.)

## What NOT to persist

- Transient UI state: validation results, loading flags, error lists, console logs.
- Derived state that can be recomputed from persisted values.

## Existing examples

| Tool | Keys |
|------|------|
| DiffViewer | `diff-textA`, `diff-textB`, `diff-mode`, `diff-lineMode` |
| JsSandbox | `js-sandbox-code` |
| OpenApiValidator | `openapi-spec`, `openapi-payload`, `openapi-schema` |
